**PRIMARY INTENT SIGNALS ⭐⭐⭐**

| Signal Category | Specific Signal | Where to Find in Clay | Why It Matters |
| ----- | ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Recent Deal Activity | Closed new acquisition in last 90 days | Pitchbook, Crunchbase, PredictLeads | Post-acquisition \= immediate need for RevOps infrastructure |
| Portfolio Company Challenges | Portfolio company posting multiple sales/marketing roles | LinkedIn (job postings), Common Room | Hiring spree \= growth pain \+ need for RevOps support |
| New Operating Partner | Hired new Operating Partner or VP Portfolio Operations in last 6 months | LinkedIn (job changes), SignalHire | New ops leader \= looking to build preferred vendor network |
| Portfolio Expansion | Increased portfolio size from 3→8+ companies in last year | Pitchbook, Affinity | More companies \= need for standardized processes |
| Value Creation Focus | PE firm mentions "value creation," "operating partner," "portfolio operations" on website/jobs | Claygent (website scraping) | Indicates active value creation playbook |

### **SECONDARY INTENT SIGNALS ⭐⭐**

*Strong indicators \- high priority*

| Signal Category | Specific Signal | Where to Find in Clay | Why It Matters |
| ----- | ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Technology Stack Gaps | Portfolio companies use different CRMs (some SF, some HubSpot, some nothing) | BuiltWith, HG Insights, Clearbit | Lack of standardization \= opportunity for you |
| International Portfolio | PE firm has 2+ portcos with international HQ or US expansion | Crunchbase, Pitchbook, LinkedIn | Your international expertise is valuable |
| Board Meeting Frequency | LinkedIn posts/updates about "board meetings," "portfolio reviews" | Claygent (LinkedIn scraping), SalesNavigator | Active portfolio management \= receptive to vendors |
| Underperforming Assets | Portfolio company had layoffs, funding down-round, or negative press | Layoffs.fyi, Crunchbase, News APIs | Underperformance \= PE needs help fixing |
| Fund Deployment Timeline | PE firm raised new fund in last 12 months | Pitchbook, Crunchbase | Fresh capital \= active deal-making \+ need for portfolio support |

* Crunchbase: HQ location, funding (US investors), acquisitions, office locations

* HG Insights: Technology adoption (US-specific SaaS tools)  
* Clearbit: Company location changes, employee growth by geography  
* Sumble  
* Hunter.io / RocketReach: Contact data (US phone numbers, US email domains)

Via Claygent (AI Web Scraper):

* Company website → scrape "About," "Contact Us," "Locations" pages for US mentions

* News/press releases → recent US expansion announcements  
* LinkedIn company page → US-based employee growth trends  
* G2/Capterra → customer review analysis for US customer mentions

Via External APIs (Custom HTTP in Clay):

* USPTO API: Trademark filings in US  
* SEC Edgar: If public, 10-K filings mentioning US expansion  
* Conference APIs: SaaStr, SaaS conferences attendance
